### TiendaBox - Pruebas del recurso Auth
@host = http://localhost:3000

### 1. Registro exitoso de cliente -> 201 Created
POST {{host}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Tomas Vallejos",
  "email": "tomas@gmail.com",
  "password": "prueba123"
}

### 2. Login cliente (debe devolver role: "cliente") -> 200 OK
POST {{host}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "tomas@gmail.com",
  "password": "prueba123"
}

### 3. Login owner (debe devolver role: "owner") -> 200 OK
POST {{host}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@tiendabox.com",
  "password": "admin123"
}

### 4. Login con password incorrecta -> 400 Bad Request ("Credenciales inválidas")
POST {{host}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "tomas@gmail.com",
  "password": "incorrecta"
}

### 5. Registro con email duplicado -> 409 Conflict
POST {{host}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Otro",
  "email": "tomas@gmail.com",
  "password": "123456"
}

### 6. Registro sin password -> 400 Bad Request
POST {{host}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Sin pass",
  "email": "sinpass@example.com"
}
